{
  "texts": [
    "After a time, travelers stopped questioning whether it was the best path.",
    "For all intents and purposes, it became the only path.",
    "This resulted in such a high volume of travelers that, at points, there still exist ruts in the trail that are more than 150 cm deep.",
    "40 The unsupervised training of LLMs results in certain paths that, like the Oregon Trail, become deeply rutted through repetition.",
    "As with the entrenchment of interpretations in scholarship through repetition, so too does that same repetition of ideas across a vast corpus of training parameters entrench an LLM's patterns of comprehension and expression."
  ]
}